result.execSummary:
The defendant Yolanda Holman was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Neglecting a Child [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.21(1)(a).
  • Neglecting a Child [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.21(1)(a).
  • Neglecting a Child [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.21(1)(a).
  • Neglecting a Child [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.21(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Original SENTENCING Transcript (28 pages) commencing 10/21/2015 received and filed.  CH
JusticePoint Pretrial Services Report received and filed.

Defendant Yolanda Holman in court with attorney Mark Allan Dluzak.  Abbey Marie DeSiato appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State advised the Court they have complied with the Victims' Rights Law.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements to the court by all parties.
Amanda Didier, Forensic Investigator present in court.
AS to count 1:  The Court sentenced the defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT of 18 MONTHS in the Wisconsin State Prisons, credit for 30 days time served.  CONFINEMENT of 12 MONTHS and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 6 MONTHS
AS to count 2:    The Court sentenced the defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT of 18 MONTHS in the Wisconsin State Prisons, consecutive to count 1, credit for 0 days time served.  CONFINEMENT of 12 MONTHS  and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 6 MONTHS.
AS to count 3:    The Court sentenced the defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT of 18 MONTHS in the Wisconsin State Prisons, consecutive to count 2, credit for 0 days time served.  CONFINEMENT of 12 MONTHS  and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 6 MONTHS.
AS to count 4:    The Court sentenced the defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT of 18 MONTHS in the Wisconsin State Prisons, concurrent with counts 1,2,3, credit for 30 days time served.  CONFINEMENT of 12 MONTHS and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 6 MONTHS with the following conditions as to all counts:
-The Court ordered that all court costs, fines, surcharges  be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of prison funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.  CASH BAIL ON DEPOSIT TO BE APPLIED.
-Pay all costs, assessments and victim/witness surcharges.
The defendant is TO BE advised of her appeal rights by defense counsel.
Defendant remanded.

Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.
